## PipelineSpec schema (informal)
- name: str
- language: "pyspark"
- source: {system: str, object_name: str}
- target: {catalog: str, schema: str, layer: "bronze"|"silver"|"gold"}
- steps: ordered list of step objects, each with a unique `id` and one `op` of:
  - read {id, source_table, alias}
  - select {id, input, columns: [{column, rename?, drop?}]}
  - filter {id, input, condition}
  - with_columns {id, input, columns: [{name, expression}]}
  - join {id, left, right, left_keys, right_keys, how, use_function?}
  - union {id, inputs: [step ids]}  (stacks streams by column name)
  - sort {id, input, columns: [{column, descending?}]}
  - distinct {id, input, columns: [key columns; empty = all]}
  - record_id {id, input, column}  (adds a sequential id column)
  - cleanse {id, input, columns?, trim?, collapse_whitespace?, remove_all_whitespace?,
    nulls_to_blank?, numeric_nulls_to_zero?, case?}  (Data Cleansing macro -> generated utility)
  - macro_call {id, input, macro}  (invokes a registered .yxmc converted to a utility)
  - aggregate {id, input, group_by, aggregations: [{column, func, alias}]}
  - call_function {id, input, function, args: {}}
  - write {id, input, target_table, mode}
- functions_used: list of function names referenced via call_function or join.use_function

